06503nam a22010215i 9781501510199DE-B159720210526051534.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210526t20202020gw     fo  d z      eng d  a2020937329  a97815015101997 a10.1515/97815015101992doi  a(DE-B1597)498268  a(OCoLC)1191231598  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aLAN0090602bisacsh00aRecent Developments in Phase Theory /ced. by Jeroen van Craenenbroeck, Cora Pots, Tanja Temmerman. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter Mouton, c[2020] 4c©2020  a1 online resource (X, 214 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aStudies in Generative Grammar [SGG] ;v13900tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tAbout the authors -- t1 Recent developments in Phase Theory Introductory remarks -- tPart I: Phases and ellipsis -- t2 Aspect interacts with phasehood: Evidence from Serbian VP-ellipsis -- t3 On top but not a phase: Phasehood inheritance and variation in sluicing -- tPart II: Domain-internal phases -- t4 Parallels in the structure of phases in clausal and nominal domains -- t5 How to detect a phase -- tPart III: Phases and labeling -- t6 On the Coordinate Structure Constraint, across-the-board-movement, phases, and labeling -- t7 Labeling as two-stage process: Evidence from semantic agreement -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe overarching goal of this volume is to explore a number of recent developments in Phase Theory (both theoretical and empirical), thus contributing to our overall understanding of the concept of phases.The volume is divided into three parts, of which the first focuses on the traditional role played by phases in defining successive cyclicity, while at the same time examining the interaction between that traditional role and Chomsky (2013)’s proposal about labeling. The second part focuses on the question of whether only the highest projection of the clausal and nominal domain, CP and DP, are phases or whether those domains also contain an internal phase: vP and NP/NumP/QP, while the third part contains two chapters that focus on the extent to which ellipsis can be used as a reliable diagnostic for phasehood.As a whole, the volume provides a detailed and in-depth view on a number of recent developments in Phase Theory, which will likely continue to dominate the debate for several years to come.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 4aAuslassung. 4aPhase Theory. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Syntax.2bisacsh  aCyclicity.  aDomain-Internal Phases.  aEllipsis.  aPhase Theory.1 aBošković, Željko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCitko, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCraenenbroeck, Jeroen van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCraenenbroeck, Jeroen van, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKučerová, Ivona, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPots, Cora, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPots, Cora, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSimpson, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSyed, Saurov, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTemmerman, Tanja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTemmerman, Tanja, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTodorović, Neda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aUrk, Coppe van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2020z978311069627108iTitle is par